{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869268618,"sessionID":"ses_285f33c83ffebugr45C3NGY0KM","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0e922d001aAHvxFuCmRbvex","messageID":"msg_d7a0cead5001RtrAnqMTit19qm","sessionID":"ses_285f33c83ffebugr45C3NGY0KM","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-377da091110f41358be2c427a53108f5","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status Commands\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta specification defines acceptance test scenarios for the `invoke` and `status` commands in the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`). These commands enable users to interact with deployed AI agents by sending payloads and checking deployment status.\n\n## Module\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md` - CLI command structure and runtime classes\n- `cli-toolkit/spec.md` - CLI requirements and scenarios\n- `deployment/client-go.md` - Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime CR\n- `python-sdk/design.md` - Python SDK client patterns\n- `python-sdk/spec.md` - SDK requirements and HTTP contracts\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `invoke` command\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` command that sends JSON payloads to a deployed agent endpoint, supporting custom HTTP headers, multiple deployment providers (AgentRuntime CR and standard K8s), and session management.\n\n### Requirement: Invoke command options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL expose a Typer command with appropriate default values for all parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Default options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube invoke` without any options\n- **WHEN** the command is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\n  - `workspace` = `\".\"` (current directory)\n  - `payload` = `\"{}\"` (empty JSON object)\n  - `header_list` = `None` (no custom headers)\n  - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (AgentRuntime CR provider)\n  - `verbose` = `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Short and long option variants\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides options using both short and long forms\n- **WHEN** parsing `invoke -f /path/to/workspace --payload '{\"key\":\"value\"}' --header 'Authorization: Bearer token' --provider k8s -v`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL correctly parse:\n  - `workspace` = `\"/path/to/workspace\"`\n  - `payload` = `'{\"key\":\"value\"}'`\n  - `header_list` = `['Authorization: Bearer token']`\n  - `provider` = `\"k8s\"`\n  - `verbose` = `True`\n\n#### Scenario: Multiple header specifications\n\n- **GIVEN** the user needs to pass multiple custom headers\n- **WHEN** the command is `invoke --header 'Authorization: Bearer token1' --header 'X-Custom-Header: value'`\n- **THEN** `header_list` SHALL be `['Authorization: Bearer token1', 'X-Custom-Header: value']`\n\n### Requirement: Payload validation and parsing\n\nThe system SHALL validate the payload format before invocation and provide clear error messages.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid JSON payload\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a valid JSON payload string\n- **WHEN** `--payload '{\"query\": \"What is AI?\", \"context\": [\"ML\"]}'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL successfully parse it into a Python dictionary and pass it to the runtime\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid JSON payload\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides an invalid JSON payload\n- **WHEN** `--payload '{invalid json}'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print \"Invalid JSON payload\" in red\n  - Exit with code `1`\n  - Not call `InvokeRuntime.invoke` or `_handle_error`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty payload default\n\n- **GIVEN** the user omits the `--payload` option\n- **WHEN** the command runs with default payload `\"{}\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL parse `\"{}\"` as an empty dictionary\n\n#### Scenario: Complex nested payload\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a complex nested JSON structure\n- **WHEN** `--payload '{\"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello\"}], \"temperature\": 0.7, \"max_tokens\": 100}'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL preserve the full structure and pass it to the runtime\n\n### Requirement: Header format validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate custom header format and provide clear error messages for malformed headers.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid header format\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides correctly formatted headers\n- **WHEN** parsing `--header 'Authorization: Bearer token'` and `--header 'Content-Type: application/json'`\n- **THEN** each header SHALL be split at the first `:` into key and value\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid header without colon\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a header string without a colon separator\n- **WHEN** `--header 'InvalidHeader'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print \"Header must be in 'key:value' format\" in red\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Header with multiple colons\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a header with colons in the value\n- **WHEN** `--header 'Authorization: Bearer:token:with:colons'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL split only at the first `:`:\n  - key = `\"Authorization\"`\n  - value = `\"Bearer:token:with:colons\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Empty header value\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a header with an empty value\n- **WHEN** `--header 'X-Custom-Header:'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - key = `\"X-Custom-Header\"`\n  - value = `\"\"` (empty string)\n\n### Requirement: Session header management\n\nThe system SHALL automatically add the session ID header when metadata contains a `session_id`.\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID from metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent metadata contains `session_id: \"abc-123-def\"`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with this metadata\n- **THEN** the HTTP request SHALL include header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: abc-123-def`\n\n#### Scenario: No session ID in metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent metadata does not contain a `session_id` field\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n- **THEN** the HTTP request SHALL NOT include the session header\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID override with custom header\n\n- **GIVEN** the metadata has `session_id: \"abc-123\"` and the user provides `--header 'X-Agentcube-Session-Id: custom-session'`\n- **WHEN** the request is constructed\n- **THEN** the custom header value SHALL take precedence over the metadata session ID\n\n### Requirement: Workspace path resolution\n\nThe system SHALL resolve the workspace path relative to the current working directory.\n\n#### Scenario: Relative workspace path\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides `-f ./my-agent`\n- **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n- **THEN** it SHALL be resolved to `{cwd}/my-agent`\n\n#### Scenario: Absolute workspace path\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides `-f /absolute/path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n- **THEN** it SHALL remain `/absolute/path/to/agent`\n\n#### Scenario: Default workspace path\n\n- **GIVEN** the user omits the `-f` option\n- **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n- **THEN** it SHALL be the current working directory `\".\"`\n\n### Requirement: Provider-specific invocation\n\nThe system SHALL route invocation requests to the appropriate endpoint based on the `provider` parameter.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube provider (default)\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` (default)\n- **WHEN** the agent is deployed as an AgentRuntime CR\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load metadata and check for `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n  - Rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n  - Include session headers if present\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes provider\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"`\n- **WHEN** the agent is deployed as a standard K8s Deployment/Service\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use the service URL from metadata (e.g., `http://localhost:{node_port}`)\n  - NOT rewrite the URL to the AgentRuntime invocation path\n  - Direct POST to the agent's endpoint\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube provider with Router URL\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and metadata contains `router_url`\n- **WHEN** invoking an agent\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the Router URL for invocation, formatted as `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n### Requirement: Invoke prerequisites validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that all prerequisites are met before attempting invocation.\n\n#### Scenario: Agent not published\n\n- **GIVEN** the workspace metadata lacks `agent_id`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating the agent must be published first\n\n#### Scenario: Missing metadata file\n\n- **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists but has no `agent_metadata.yaml` (or fallbacks)\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating metadata file is missing\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid workspace path\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid provider value\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides an invalid provider value\n- **WHEN** `--provider invalid-provider` is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL validate and reject the provider value\n\n### Requirement: Invoke response handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle and display invocation responses appropriately.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful invocation\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent endpoint returns a successful response (2xx)\n- **WHEN** the invocation completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the response in a formatted manner\n\n#### Scenario: Agent returns error response\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent endpoint returns an error response (4xx or 5xx)\n- **WHEN** the invocation completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display the error message and response details\n\n#### Scenario: Network timeout\n\n- **GIVEN** the invocation request times out\n- **WHEN** the timeout period elapses\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a timeout exception, which shall be handled by `_handle_error`\n\n### Requirement: Error handling for invoke\n\nThe system SHALL use consistent error handling patterns for all exceptions.\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime exception\n\n- **GIVEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` raises a `RuntimeError`\n- **WHEN** the exception is caught by the CLI\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n  - Print \"Error invoke: {error_message}\" in red\n  - If `verbose` is `True`, print the full traceback\n  - Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n\n#### Scenario: HTTP connection error\n\n- **GIVEN** there is a network connectivity issue\n- **WHEN** the invocation attempt fails\n- **THEN** the system SHALL catch the connection error and surface it via `_handle_error`\n\n#### Scenario: Subcommand verbose logging\n\n- **GIVEN** the user uses the local `--verbose` flag on the `invoke` command\n- **WHEN** an error occurs\n- **THEN** the traceback SHALL be printed even if the global `-v` was not passed\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: `status` command\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `status` command that displays the current state of a deployed agent, including deployment information, health status, and endpoint details.\n\n### Requirement: Status command options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL expose a Typer command with appropriate default values for all parameters.\n\n#### Scenario: Default options\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube status` without any options\n- **WHEN** the command is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\n  - `workspace` = `\".\"` (current directory)\n  - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (AgentRuntime CR provider)\n  - `verbose` = `False`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom workspace and provider\n\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies custom options\n- **WHEN** parsing `status -f /path/to/workspace --provider k8s`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use:\n  - `workspace` = `\"/path/to/workspace\"`\n  - `provider` = `\"k8s\"`\n  - `verbose` = `False`\n\n### Requirement: Status display formatting\n\nThe system SHALL display agent status in a Rich `Table` with clear, readable formatting.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful status retrieval\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent is successfully deployed and status is available\n- **WHEN** `status` runs and retrieves status information\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display a Rich `Table` containing:\n  - Field names in the first column\n  - Field values in the second column\n  - Key information: agent name, namespace, status, endpoint, deployment details\n\n#### Scenario: Status table fields\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent status is retrieved\n- **WHEN** the Rich table is rendered\n- **THEN** it SHALL include these fields when available:\n  - Agent Name\n  - Namespace\n  - Status (e.g., \"running\", \"ready\", \"error\", \"not_published\")\n  - Agent Endpoint\n  - Session ID (if applicable)\n  - Deployment Type (AgentRuntime or Deployment/Service)\n  - Image URL\n  - Version\n\n#### Scenario: Status not published\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent metadata has no `agent_id` field\n- **WHEN** `status` is called and returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print a message indicating the agent is not published\n  - Provide guidance to run `publish` command first\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n### Requirement: Status for AgentCube provider\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve and display status for agents deployed via the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR).\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR with status\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and the AgentRuntime CR exists with status\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present\n- **THEN** the system SHALL extract `status` and `agentEndpoint` from the CR status\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR created but no status\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and the AgentRuntime CR exists but has no status field\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return status `\"created_no_status\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR not found\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` and the AgentRuntime CR does not exist\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return status `\"not_found_in_k8s\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR error status\n\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR status indicates an error condition\n- **WHEN** status is retrieved\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display error details and exit with code `1`\n\n### Requirement: Status for Kubernetes provider\n\nThe system SHALL retrieve and display status for agents deployed via the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + Service).\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment and service status\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and the agent is deployed with Deployment and Service\n- **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL query both Deployment and Service status\n- **THEN** the status SHALL include:\n  - Deployment ready replicas\n  - Service node port\n  - Service URL\n  - Pod status summary\n\n#### Scenario: K8s deployment not ready\n\n- **GIVEN** the Deployment exists but replicas are not ready\n- **WHEN** status is retrieved\n- **THEN** the status SHALL indicate `\"not_ready\"` with details about current vs. desired replicas\n\n#### Scenario: K8s resources not found\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"` and neither Deployment nor Service exists\n- **WHEN** status is retrieved\n- **THEN** the status SHALL indicate `\"not_found_in_k8s\"`\n\n### Requirement: Status exit codes\n\nThe system SHALL use appropriate exit codes to indicate the result of status checks.\n\n#### Scenario: Successful status (agent running)\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent status indicates it is running or ready\n- **WHEN** `status` completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with code `0`\n\n#### Scenario: Agent not published\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent has no `agent_id` in metadata\n- **WHEN** `status` completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Agent in error state\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent status indicates an error condition\n- **WHEN** `status` completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Agent not found in Kubernetes\n\n- **GIVEN** the agent was previously published but the CR or Deployment no longer exists\n- **WHEN** `status` completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n\n### Requirement: Workspace path resolution for status\n\nThe system SHALL resolve the workspace path for status checks.\n\n#### Scenario: Default workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status` without `-f` option\n- **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n- **THEN** it SHALL use the current working directory `\".\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom workspace path\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status -f /path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `/path/to/agent`\n\n#### Scenario: Missing workspace\n\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `status` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a `ValueError` indicating the directory does not exist\n\n### Requirement: Verbose logging for status\n\nThe system SHALL provide detailed logging when verbose mode is enabled.\n\n#### Scenario: Verbose status output\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status --verbose`\n- **WHEN** status is retrieved\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log additional details about:\n  - Kubernetes API calls\n  - CR or resource retrieval\n  - Status parsing\n  - Any warnings or additional information\n\n### Requirement: Error handling for status\n\nThe system SHALL use consistent error handling patterns for all exceptions.\n\n#### Scenario: Status retrieval exception\n\n- **GIVEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` raises a `RuntimeError`\n- **WHEN** the exception is caught by the CLI\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n  - Print \"Error status: {error_message}\" in red\n  - If `verbose` is `True`, print the full traceback\n  - Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes connection error\n\n- **GIVEN** there is an issue connecting to the Kubernetes API\n- **WHEN** `status` attempts to query the cluster\n- **THEN** the system SHALL catch the connection error and surface it via `_handle_error`\n\n#### Scenario: Metadata validation error\n\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but contains invalid data\n- **WHEN** `status` attempts to load metadata\n- **THEN** the system SHALL catch the validation error and surface it via `_handle_error`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Cross-cutting concerns\n\n### Requirement: Metadata file loading\n\nThe system SHALL load agent metadata from the workspace with appropriate fallback behavior.\n\n#### Scenario: Primary metadata file exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** metadata is loaded for `invoke` or `status`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario: Primary missing, first fallback\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist but `agent.yaml` does\n- **WHEN** metadata is loaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load from `agent.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario: Primary and first fallback missing\n\n- **GIVEN** neither `agent_metadata.yaml` nor `agent.yaml` exists but `metadata.yaml` does\n- **WHEN** metadata is loaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load from `metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario: No metadata file found\n\n- **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** metadata is loaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating no metadata file was found\n\n### Requirement: Global verbose logging propagation\n\nThe system SHALL correctly propagate verbose logging settings from the root callback to subcommands.\n\n#### Scenario: Global verbose with subcommand verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** the user passes both global `-v` and local `--verbose` on `invoke` or `status`\n- **WHEN** the command runs\n- **THEN** verbose logging SHALL be enabled\n\n#### Scenario: Subcommand verbose without global verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** the user passes only `invoke --verbose` without global `-v`\n- **WHEN** the command runs\n- **THEN** verbose logging SHALL be enabled for that subcommand\n\n#### Scenario: Global verbose without subcommand verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** the user passes only global `-v` without subcommand `--verbose`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` or `status` runs\n- **THEN** verbose logging SHALL be enabled\n\n### Requirement: Rich output formatting\n\nThe system SHALL use Rich library for consistent, readable command output.\n\n#### Scenario: Rich table for status\n\n- **GIVEN** status information is available\n- **WHEN** displaying status\n- **THEN** the output SHALL be formatted as a Rich table with proper styling\n\n#### Scenario: Rich console for errors\n\n- **GIVEN** an error occurs\n- **WHEN** the error is displayed\n- **THEN** error messages SHALL use Rich console for red-colored output\n\n#### Scenario: Rich progress spinner\n\n- **GIVEN** a long-running operation (e.g., waiting for status)\n- **WHEN** the operation is in progress\n- **THEN** the system SHALL display a Rich Progress spinner\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Integration scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Invoke after successful publish\n\nThe system SHALL support invoking an agent that has been successfully published.\n\n#### Scenario: Full workflow - pack, build, publish, invoke\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid agent workspace\n- **WHEN** the user runs:\n  1. `pack` - successfully packages the workspace\n  2. `build` - successfully builds the image\n  3. `publish --provider agentcube` - successfully deploys to Kubernetes\n  4. `invoke --payload '{\"query\": \"test\"}'` - sends a payload\n- **THEN** each command SHALL complete successfully\n- **THEN** `invoke` SHALL receive a response from the deployed agent\n\n#### Scenario: Invoke after local build publish\n\n- **GIVEN** an agent built in local mode\n- **WHEN** published with `--image-url` and `--provider k8s`\n- **THEN** `invoke --provider k8s` SHALL successfully send requests to the NodePort service\n\n### Requirement: Status checks during deployment lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL allow status checks at various stages of the agent lifecycle.\n\n#### Scenario: Status before publish\n\n- **GIVEN** an agent has been packed but not published\n- **WHEN** `status` is run\n- **THEN** the system SHALL indicate the agent is not published and exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario: Status during deployment rollout\n\n- **GIVEN** an agent has been published and is in the process of becoming ready\n- **WHEN** `status` is run\n- **THEN** the system SHALL show the current deployment state (e.g., \"not_ready\")\n\n#### Scenario: Status after agent is ready\n\n- **GIVEN** an agent deployment has completed successfully\n- **WHEN** `status` is run\n- **THEN** the system SHALL show status \"ready\" or \"running\" with full endpoint information\n\n### Requirement: Session management across invokes\n\nThe system SHALL maintain session consistency across multiple invocations.\n\n#### Scenario: Reuse session ID from metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** the first `invoke` establishes a session and saves `session_id` to metadata\n- **WHEN** subsequent `invoke` commands are run without specifying a new session\n- **THEN** each invocation SHALL use the existing `session_id` from metadata\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID in headers\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id: \"existing-session\"`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called with `--header 'X-Agentcube-Session-Id: new-session'`\n- **THEN** the custom header SHALL override the metadata session ID for that specific request\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Edge cases and error conditions\n\n### Requirement: Malformed metadata\n\nThe system SHALL handle malformed or incomplete metadata gracefully.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing required fields in metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but lacks required fields (e.g., `agent_name`)\n- **WHEN** `invoke` or `status` attempts to load metadata\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a validation error indicating which fields are missing\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid data types in metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file contains fields with invalid data types\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise a validation error with details about the type mismatch\n\n### Requirement: Concurrent invocations\n\nThe system SHALL handle multiple concurrent invocations to the same agent.\n\n#### Scenario: Multiple invocations in parallel\n\n- **GIVEN** an agent is deployed and ready\n- **WHEN** multiple `invoke` commands are run simultaneously against the same agent\n- **THEN** each invocation SHALL receive its own response\n- **THEN** session headers SHALL be correctly applied to each request\n\n### Requirement: Large payloads\n\nThe system SHALL handle large JSON payloads within reasonable limits.\n\n#### Scenario: Large JSON payload\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a large JSON payload (e.g., 1MB)\n- **WHEN** `invoke --payload` is called with the large payload\n- **THEN** the system SHALL successfully parse and send the payload to the agent endpoint\n\n#### Scenario: Extremely large payload rejection\n\n- **GIVEN** the user provides an extremely large JSON payload exceeding system limits\n- **WHEN** `invoke --payload` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL reject the payload with an appropriate error message\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Provider-specific edge cases\n\n### Requirement: AgentCube provider edge cases\n\nThe system SHALL handle edge cases specific to the AgentCube provider.\n\n#### Scenario: Missing router_url for AgentCube provider\n\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` but metadata lacks `router_url`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` attempts to construct the invocation URL\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise an error indicating `router_url` is required for AgentCube provider\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR with missing status field\n\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists but has no status field in its spec\n- **WHEN** `status` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL handle gracefully and return appropriate status\n\n### Requirement: Kubernetes provider edge cases\n\nThe system SHALL handle edge cases specific to the standard Kubernetes provider.\n\n#### Scenario: NodePort outside valid range\n\n- **GIVEN** a K8s deployment was created with an invalid NodePort\n- **WHEN** `invoke --provider k8s` attempts to connect\n- **THEN** the system SHALL handle connection errors appropriately\n\n#### Scenario: Service with no endpoints\n\n- **GIVEN** the K8s Service exists but has no ready endpoints\n- **WHEN** `invoke --provider k8s` attempts to connect\n- **THEN** the system SHALL handle connection errors and provide informative messages\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n### Invoke Command\n\n- [ ] Command accepts all required and optional parameters with correct defaults\n- [ ] Invalid JSON payloads are rejected with clear error messages\n- [ ] Invalid header formats are rejected with clear error messages\n- [ ] Session headers are automatically added when `session_id` exists in metadata\n- [ ] Workspace paths are resolved correctly (relative and absolute)\n- [ ] AgentCube provider routes to AgentRuntime invocation endpoint\n- [ ] K8s provider routes directly to service endpoint\n- [ ] Prerequisites are validated before invocation attempts\n- [ ] Successful responses are displayed in a readable format\n- [ ] Error responses and timeouts are handled gracefully\n- [ ] Verbose mode provides detailed logging and traces\n- [ ] Exit code `0` on success, `1` on failure\n\n### Status Command\n\n- [ ] Command accepts all required and optional parameters with correct defaults\n- [ ] Status is displayed in a Rich table with clear formatting\n- [ ] \"Not published\" state is detected and reported with guidance\n- [ ] AgentRuntime CR status is correctly retrieved and parsed\n- [ ] K8s Deployment/Service status is correctly retrieved and parsed\n- [ ] Exit code `0` on success/ready, `1` on failure/not-ready/not-published\n- [ ] Workspace paths are resolved correctly\n- [ ] Verbose mode provides additional debugging information\n- [ ] Errors are caught and surfaced via `_handle_error`\n\n### Cross-Cutting\n\n- [ ] Metadata loading with fallback behavior works correctly\n- [ ] Global and subcommand verbose flags interact correctly\n- [ ] Rich formatting is used consistently across output\n- [ ] Full workflow (pack → build → publish → invoke/status) works end-to-end\n- [ ] Session management maintains consistency across invocations\n- [ ] Edge cases are handled gracefully with informative errors\n- [ ] Provider-specific edge cases are handled correctly","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775869268608,"end":1775869268614}}}}
