{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869274220,"sessionID":"ses_285f33c83ffebugr45C3NGY0KM","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0ea83100174hcLA9sTKadvG","messageID":"msg_d7a0e9d58001ybSUfmB2UVBP1j","sessionID":"ses_285f33c83ffebugr45C3NGY0KM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9f4215326ee348f6bc03acbfa0631152","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # delta-spec.md — AR-020: CLI pack 命令\n2: \n3: ## Module: `cmd/cli`\n4: \n5: ## Delta Overview\n6: \n7: Add the `pack` command to the AgentCube CLI for validating and preparing agent workspaces, merging CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generating Dockerfiles, and reporting paths.\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## REQ-001: Pack command initialization\n12: \n13: ### Requirement: Pack command registration and default options\n14: \n15: System SHALL provide a `pack` command that validates and prepares agent workspaces with configurable options.\n16: \n17: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n18: - Command name: `pack`\n19: - Supports workspace path specification\n20: - Supports metadata field overrides via CLI options\n21: - Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\n22: - Supports custom output path specification\n23: \n24: **Scenarios:**\n25: \n26: #### Scenario 1.1: Command registration and default options\n27: - **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\n28: - **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack` without options\n29: - **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\n30:   - `workspace`: `\".\"` (current directory)\n31:   - `agent_name`: `None`\n32:   - `language`: `None`\n33:   - `entrypoint`: `None`\n34:   - `port`: `None`\n35:   - `build_mode`: `None`\n36:   - `description`: `None`\n37:   - `output`: `None`\n38:   - `verbose`: `False`\n39: \n40: #### Scenario 1.2: Command option validation\n41: - **GIVEN** the user provides CLI options\n42: - **WHEN** options include `--workspace`, `--agent-name`, `--language`, `--entrypoint`, `--port`, `--build-mode`, `--description`, `--output`, `--verbose`\n43: - **THEN** the system SHALL accept all valid option values:\n44:   - `workspace`: string path to workspace directory\n45:   - `agent_name`: string or None\n46:   - `language`: string (python/java) or None\n47:   - `entrypoint`: string command or None\n48:   - `port`: integer (1-65535) or None\n49:   - `build_mode`: string (local/cloud) or None\n50:   - `description`: string or None\n51:   - `output`: string path or None\n52:   - `verbose`: boolean flag\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## REQ-002: Workspace validation\n57: \n58: ### Requirement: Workspace structure validation\n59: \n60: System SHALL validate that the workspace path exists, is a directory, and contains required files for the specified language.\n61: \n62: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n63: - Validates workspace path existence and type\n64: - Language-specific file presence checks\n65: - Clear error messages for validation failures\n66: \n67: **Scenarios:**\n68: \n69: #### Scenario 2.1: Workspace path exists and is a directory\n70: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n71: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` is called\n72: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n73:   - Verify the path exists\n74:   - Verify it is a directory\n75:   - Raise `ValueError` with message \"Directory does not exist\" if path does not exist\n76:   - Raise `ValueError` with message \"Path is not a directory\" if path is not a directory\n77: \n78: #### Scenario 2.2: Python workspace validation\n79: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n80: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` is called\n81: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n82:   - Search for at least one `*.py` file in the workspace root\n83:   - Raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` if no Python files exist\n84:   - Validate `requirements.txt` exists if specified in metadata\n85:   - Accept workspace structure as valid if at least one Python file is found\n86: \n87: #### Scenario 2.3: Java workspace validation\n88: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n89: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility` is called\n90: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n91:   - Verify `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root\n92:   - Raise `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")` if missing\n93:   - Accept workspace structure as valid if pom.xml exists\n94: \n95: #### Scenario 2.4: Missing workspace\n96: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n97: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime.pack` is called\n98: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n99:   - Raise `ValueError` with message indicating directory does not exist\n100:   - Propagate error to CLI handler which prints error in red\n101:   - Exit with code `1`\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## REQ-003: Metadata loading and creation\n106: \n107: ### Requirement: Metadata file loading and creation\n108: \n109: System SHALL load existing metadata from workspace files or create new metadata with sensible defaults.\n110: \n111: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n112: - Supports multiple metadata filename fallbacks\n113: - Creates new metadata with defaults when none exists\n114: - Validates loaded metadata against schema\n115: \n116: **Scenarios:**\n117: \n118: #### Scenario 3.1: Load existing metadata from file\n119: - **GIVEN** a workspace with existing `agent_metadata.yaml`\n120: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n121: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n122:   - Attempt to load `agent_metadata.yaml` first\n123:   - Fall back to `agent.yaml` if primary not found\n124:   - Fall back to `metadata.yaml` if previous not found\n125:   - Parse YAML content into `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n126:   - Validate all fields against Pydantic validators\n127:   - Return loaded metadata object\n128: \n129: #### Scenario 3.2: Create new metadata for new workspace\n130: - **GIVEN** a workspace without any metadata file\n131: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` is called\n132: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n133:   - Detect no metadata file exists\n134:   - Create new `AgentMetadata` instance with defaults:\n135:     - `agent_name`: inferred from workspace directory name\n136:     - `language`: `\"python\"` or from CLI option\n137:     - `entrypoint`: inferred from workspace structure\n138:     - `port`: `8080`\n139:     - `build_mode`: `\"local\"`\n140:   - Return new metadata object\n141: \n142: #### Scenario 3.3: Metadata field validation\n143: - **GIVEN** metadata loaded from YAML file\n144: - **WHEN** fields violate Pydantic validators\n145: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n146:   - Reject unsupported `language` values (must be `python` or `java`)\n147:   - Reject unsupported `build_mode` values (must be `local` or `cloud`)\n148:   - Reject `port` values outside range 1-65535\n149:   - Raise validation error with field-specific message\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ## REQ-004: CLI option overrides\n154: \n155: ### Requirement: Metadata field overrides from CLI options\n156: \n157: System SHALL apply CLI option overrides to loaded metadata, allowing users to override any metadata field.\n158: \n159: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n160: - Supports overriding individual metadata fields\n161: - Validates overridden field values\n162: - Preserves non-overridden fields\n163: \n164: **Scenarios:**\n165: \n166: #### Scenario 4.1: Apply agent_name override\n167: - **GIVEN** loaded metadata with `agent_name = \"old-name\"`\n168: - **WHEN** user provides `--agent-name \"new-name\"`\n169: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n170:   - Override metadata.agent_name to \"new-name\"\n171:   - Keep all other metadata fields unchanged\n172: \n173: #### Scenario 4.2: Apply language override\n174: - **GIVEN** loaded metadata with `language = \"python\"`\n175: - **WHEN** user provides `--language java`\n176: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n177:   - Override metadata.language to \"java\"\n178:   - Validate new language value\n179:   - Keep all other metadata fields unchanged\n180: \n181: #### Scenario 4.3: Apply entrypoint override\n182: - **GIVEN** loaded metadata with `entrypoint = \"python main.py\"`\n183: - **WHEN** user provides `--entrypoint \"java -jar app.jar\"`\n184: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n185:   - Override metadata.entrypoint to \"java -jar app.jar\"\n186:   - Keep all other metadata fields unchanged\n187: \n188: #### Scenario 4.4: Apply port override\n189: - **GIVEN** loaded metadata with `port = 8080`\n190: - **WHEN** user provides `--port 9000`\n191: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n192:   - Override metadata.port to 9000\n193:   - Validate port is within 1-65535\n194:   - Keep all other metadata fields unchanged\n195: \n196: #### Scenario 4.5: Apply build_mode override\n197: - **GIVEN** loaded metadata with `build_mode = \"local\"`\n198: - **WHEN** user provides `--build-mode cloud`\n199: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n200:   - Override metadata.build_mode to \"cloud\"\n201:   - Validate build_mode is \"local\" or \"cloud\"\n202:   - Keep all other metadata fields unchanged\n203: \n204: #### Scenario 4.6: Apply description override\n205: - **GIVEN** loaded metadata with `description = None`\n206: - **WHEN** user provides `--description \"My custom agent\"`\n207: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n208:   - Override metadata.description to \"My custom agent\"\n209:   - Keep all other metadata fields unchanged\n210: \n211: #### Scenario 4.7: No CLI overrides provided\n212: - **GIVEN** loaded metadata with existing values\n213: - **WHEN** user runs pack without any CLI options\n214: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n215:   - Keep all metadata fields unchanged\n216:   - Use existing metadata values\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## REQ-005: Language-specific processing\n221: \n222: ### Requirement: Dependency processing for Python and Java\n223: \n224: System SHALL process language-specific dependency files and store dependency information in metadata.\n225: \n226: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n227: - Processes Python requirements.txt files\n228: - Processes Java pom.xml files\n229: - Validates dependency formats\n230: - Stores dependency information in metadata\n231: \n232: **Scenarios:**\n233: \n234: #### Scenario 5.1: Process Python dependencies\n235: - **GIVEN** a Python workspace with `requirements.txt`\n236: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies` is called\n237: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n238:   - Read `requirements.txt` if it exists\n239:   - Parse each dependency line\n240:   - Validate dependency format\n241:   - Store dependency information in metadata\n242:   - Skip processing if `requirements.txt` does not exist\n243: \n244: #### Scenario 5.2: Process Java dependencies\n245: - **GIVEN** a Java workspace with `pom.xml`\n246: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_java_dependencies` is called\n247: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n248:   - Parse `pom.xml` using XML parser\n249:   - Extract dependency information from `<dependencies>` section\n250:   - Extract groupId, artifactId, version for each dependency\n251:   - Store dependency information in metadata\n252:   - Skip processing if `pom.xml` does not exist\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## REQ-006: Dockerfile generation\n257: \n258: ### Requirement: Dockerfile generation for Python and Java\n259: \n260: System SHALL generate appropriate Dockerfiles for Python and Java workspaces based on metadata and workspace structure.\n261: \n262: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n263: - Generates valid Python Dockerfiles\n264: - Generates valid Java Dockerfiles\n265: - Infers default entrypoints when not specified\n266: - Skips generation if Dockerfile already exists\n267: \n268: **Scenarios:**\n269: \n270: #### Scenario 6.1: Generate Python Dockerfile\n271: - **GIVEN** metadata with `language = \"python\"`\n272: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` is called\n273: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n274:   - Call `_generate_python_dockerfile` to create Dockerfile content\n275:   - Create Dockerfile content with:\n276:     - Base Python image (e.g., `python:3.10-slim`)\n277:     - Work directory setup\n278:     - Dependency installation from requirements.txt\n279:     - Application file copying\n280:     - Entrypoint command from metadata\n281:   - Write Dockerfile to workspace root\n282:   - Return path to generated Dockerfile\n283: \n284: #### Scenario 6.2: Generate Java Dockerfile\n285: - **GIVEN** metadata with `language = \"java\"`\n286: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` is called\n287: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n288:   - Call `_generate_java_dockerfile` to create Dockerfile content\n289:   - Create Dockerfile content with:\n290:     - Base Java image (e.g., `openjdk:17-slim`)\n291:     - Work directory setup\n292:     - Maven build execution (copy pom.xml, run mvn package)\n293:     - Artifact copying from target directory\n294:     - Entrypoint command from metadata\n295:   - Write Dockerfile to workspace root\n296:   - Return path to generated Dockerfile\n297: \n298: #### Scenario 6.3: Infer entrypoint for Python\n299: - **GIVEN** a Python workspace with `main.py` present\n300: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` is called\n301: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n302:   - Check for `main.py` in workspace root\n303:   - Return \"python main.py\" if found\n304:   - Check for other common entrypoints if main.py not found\n305:   - Return default \"python -m main\" if no specific entrypoint found\n306: \n307: #### Scenario 6.4: Infer entrypoint for Java\n308: - **GIVEN** a Java workspace with compiled JAR\n309: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` is called\n310: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n311:   - Check for `target/*.jar` files\n312:   - Return \"java -jar target/<jar-name>.jar\" if found\n313:   - Return default \"java -jar target/app.jar\" if no specific JAR found\n314: \n315: #### Scenario 6.5: Skip Dockerfile generation\n316: - **GIVEN** metadata with existing Dockerfile path\n317: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` is called\n318: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n319:   - Skip Dockerfile generation if one already exists\n320:   - Return path to existing Dockerfile\n321:   - Not overwrite existing Dockerfile\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ## REQ-007: Metadata update and save\n326: \n327: ### Requirement: Metadata persistence\n328: \n329: System SHALL save updated metadata to the workspace with appropriate formatting and file permissions.\n330: \n331: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n332: - Saves metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n333: - Uses appropriate YAML formatting\n334: - Excludes None values from output\n335: - Creates parent directories if needed\n336: \n337: **Scenarios:**\n338: \n339: #### Scenario 7.1: Update pack metadata\n340: - **GIVEN** processed metadata and generated Dockerfile path\n341: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata` is called\n342: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n343:   - Update metadata with Dockerfile information\n344:   - Store Dockerfile path in metadata\n345:   - Update pack timestamp in metadata\n346:   - Save metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml`\n347: \n348: #### Scenario 7.2: Save metadata to file\n349: - **GIVEN** updated metadata object\n350: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` is called\n351: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n352:   - Write metadata to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n353:   - Use YAML format with `default_flow_style=False`\n354:   - Use `indent=2` for readability\n355:   - Use `sort_keys=False` to preserve field order\n356:   - Exclude None fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n357:   - Create parent directories if they don't exist\n358: \n359: ---\n360: \n361: ## REQ-008: Output path handling\n362: \n363: ### Requirement: Custom output path support\n364: \n365: System SHALL support custom output paths for packaged workspaces, creating directories as needed.\n366: \n367: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n368: - Uses workspace path as default output\n369: - Supports custom output path specification\n370: - Creates output directories if needed\n371: - Validates output path type\n372: \n373: **Scenarios:**\n374: \n375: #### Scenario 8.1: Use default output path\n376: - **GIVEN** a workspace path `/path/to/workspace`\n377: - **WHEN** user does not provide `--output` option\n378: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n379:   - Use workspace path as output path\n380:   - Return `/path/to/workspace` as final output path\n381: \n382: #### Scenario 8.2: Use custom output path\n383: - **GIVEN** a workspace path `/path/to/workspace`\n384: - **WHEN** user provides `--output /path/to/output`\n385: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n386:   - Use `/path/to/output` as output path\n387:   - Create output directory if it doesn't exist\n388:   - Return `/path/to/output` as final output path\n389: \n390: #### Scenario 8.3: Prepare output path\n391: - **GIVEN** an output path that may not exist\n392: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` is called\n393: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n394:   - Check if output path exists\n395:   - Create directory structure if it doesn't exist\n396:   - Raise error if path exists but is not a directory\n397:   - Return normalized absolute path\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ## REQ-009: Success reporting\n402: \n403: ### Requirement: User-friendly success messages\n404: \n405: System SHALL display clear, formatted success messages with relevant information when pack completes successfully.\n406: \n407: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n408: - Displays success message in formatted output\n409: - Shows agent_name, workspace_path, and metadata_path\n410: - Uses Rich Progress spinner during processing\n411: - Supports verbose mode for detailed output\n412: \n413: **Scenarios:**\n414: \n415: #### Scenario 9.1: Successful pack completion\n416: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n417: - **WHEN** `pack` command completes without exception\n418: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n419:   - Display success message using Rich console\n420:   - Show agent_name from metadata\n421:   - Show resolved workspace_path\n422:   - Show metadata_path as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n423:   - Use Rich Progress spinner during workspace processing\n424:   - Display completion status in green\n425: \n426: #### Scenario 9.2: Verbose output enabled\n427: - **GIVEN** user passes `--verbose` flag\n428: - **WHEN** `pack` command runs\n429: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n430:   - Enable detailed logging at DEBUG level\n431:   - Log each step of the pack process\n432:   - Show detailed workspace structure information\n433:   - Show metadata validation results\n434:   - Show dependency processing details\n435:   - Show Dockerfile generation progress\n436: \n437: ---\n438: \n439: ## REQ-010: Error handling\n440: \n441: ### Requirement: Comprehensive error handling and reporting\n442: \n443: System SHALL handle errors gracefully with clear messages and appropriate exit codes.\n444: \n445: **Acceptance Criteria:**\n446: - Displays error messages in red\n447: - Shows tracebacks in verbose mode\n448: - Exits with code 1 on errors\n449: - Validates input before processing\n450: \n451: **Scenarios:**\n452: \n453: #### Scenario 10.1: Pack failure with verbose enabled\n454: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n455: - **WHEN** user has passed `--verbose` flag\n456: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n457:   - Print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red\n458:   - Print full exception traceback\n459:   - Exit with code `1`\n460: \n461: #### Scenario 10.2: Pack failure without verbose\n462: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n463: - **WHEN** user has not passed `--verbose` flag\n464: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n465:   - Print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red\n466:   - Not print traceback\n467:   - Exit with code `1`\n468: \n469: #### Scenario 10.3: Invalid JSON in metadata file\n470: - **GIVEN** a metadata file with invalid YAML syntax\n471: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` attempts to parse\n472: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n473:   - Raise YAML parsing error\n474:   - Propagate error to CLI handler\n475:   - Print error message indicating YAML parsing failure\n476:   - Exit with code `1`\n477: \n478: #### Scenario 10.4: Missing required fields in metadata\n479: - **GIVEN** metadata loaded without required fields (e.g., agent_name, entrypoint)\n480: - **WHEN** validation occurs\n481: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n482:   - Detect missing required fields\n483:   - Raise validation error listing missing fields\n484:   - Propagate error to CLI handler\n485:   - Print error message in red\n486:   - Exit with code `1`\n487: \n488: ---\n489: \n490: ## Integration Scenarios\n491: \n492: ### INT-001: CLI to PackRuntime Integration\n493: \n494: #### Scenario INT-1.1: CLI creates PackRuntime instance\n495: - **GIVEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack` with options\n496: - **WHEN** CLI handler processes command\n497: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n498:   - Create `PackRuntime` instance\n499:   - Pass `verbose` flag from CLI option\n500:   - Call `pack()` method on instance\n501:   - Pass workspace path and options dictionary\n502: \n503: #### Scenario INT-1.2: PackRuntime returns result to CLI\n504: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack()` completes successfully\n505: - **WHEN** method returns\n506: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n507:   - Return dictionary with:\n508:     - `agent_name`: string\n509:     - `workspace_path`: Path object\n510:     - `metadata_path`: Path object\n511:   - CLI formats and displays result\n512:   - CLI exits with code `0`\n513: \n514: ### INT-002: PackRuntime to MetadataService Integration\n515: \n516: #### Scenario INT-2.1: Load metadata via service\n517: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` needs metadata\n518: - **WHEN** method calls service\n519: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n520:   - Call `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)`\n521:   - Receive `AgentMetadata` object\n522:   - Handle exceptions if metadata cannot be loaded\n523: \n524: #### Scenario INT-2.2: Save metadata via service\n525: - **GIVEN** updated metadata needs to be persisted\n526: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata` calls service\n527: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n528:   - Call `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)`\n529:   - Verify file was written successfully\n530:   - Handle exceptions if save fails\n531: \n532: ### INT-003: PackRuntime to Docker Generation Integration\n533: \n534: #### Scenario INT-3.1: Dockerfile generation completes\n535: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` is called\n536: - **WHEN** generation completes\n537: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n538:   - Return path to generated Dockerfile\n539:   - Include Dockerfile path in metadata\n540:   - Continue with rest of pack process\n541: \n542: #### Scenario INT-3.2: Dockerfile generation fails\n543: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` encounters error\n544: - **WHEN** error occurs during generation\n545: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n546:   - Raise exception with descriptive message\n547:   - Propagate error to pack method\n548:   - Handle error at CLI level with appropriate exit code\n549: \n550: ---\n551: \n552: ## Technical Constraints\n553: \n554: ### Requirement: Language and dependencies\n555: \n556: System SHALL use Python 3.10+ and the following dependencies:\n557: \n558: **Dependencies:**\n559: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` for CLI framework\n560: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` for data validation\n561: - `pyyaml>=6.0` for YAML parsing\n562: - `rich>=13.0.0` for formatted console output\n563: - `packaging>=23.0` for version handling\n564: \n565: ### Requirement: File locations\n566: \n567: - CLI command definition: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n568: - PackRuntime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n569: - MetadataService implementation: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n570: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n571: - Metadata filename: `agent_metadata.yaml`\n572: \n573: ### Requirement: Exit codes\n574: \n575: System SHALL return appropriate exit codes:\n576: - Exit code 0 for successful pack operations\n577: - Exit code 1 for pack failures\n578: - Exit code 130 for SIGINT (Ctrl+C) interruption\n579: \n580: ---\n581: \n582: ## Testing Requirements\n583: \n584: ### Unit Test Scenarios\n585: \n586: #### Scenario UT-1.1: Test workspace structure validation\n587: - **GIVEN** a test suite for `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure`\n588: - **WHEN** tests run\n589: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n590:   - Valid directory path passes validation\n591:   - Non-existent path raises ValueError\n592:   - Non-directory path raises ValueError\n593:   - Python workspace with .py files passes validation\n594:   - Python workspace without .py files raises ValueError\n595:   - Java workspace with pom.xml passes validation\n596:   - Java workspace without pom.xml raises ValueError\n597: \n598: #### Scenario UT-1.2: Test metadata loading\n599: - **GIVEN** a test suite for `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata`\n600: - **WHEN** tests run\n601: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n602:   - Loading existing agent_metadata.yaml\n603:   - Loading fallback agent.yaml\n604:   - Loading fallback metadata.yaml\n605:   - Creating new metadata when no file exists\n606:   - Invalid YAML raises appropriate error\n607:   - Invalid metadata values raise validation errors\n608: \n609: #### Scenario UT-1.3: Test option overrides\n610: - **GIVEN** a test suite for `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides`\n611: - **WHEN** tests run\n612: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n613:   - Single option override\n614:   - Multiple option overrides\n615:   - No option overrides\n616:   - Invalid option values raise errors\n617: \n618: #### Scenario UT-1.4: Test Dockerfile generation\n619: - **GIVEN** a test suite for Dockerfile generation methods\n620: - **WHEN** tests run\n621: - **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n622:   - Python Dockerfile generation with requirements.txt\n623:   - Python Dockerfile generation without requirements.txt\n624:   - Java Dockerfile generation with pom.xml\n625:   - Java Dockerfile generation without pom.xml\n626:   - Entrypoint inference for Python\n627:   - Entrypoint inference for Java\n628: \n629: ### Integration Test Scenarios\n630: \n631: #### Scenario IT-1.1: End-to-end pack for Python agent\n632: - **GIVEN** a Python workspace with valid structure\n633: - **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack`\n634: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n635:   - Successfully validate workspace\n636:   - Load or create metadata\n637:   - Process Python dependencies\n638:   - Generate Dockerfile\n639:   - Save updated metadata\n640:   - Display success message with paths\n641: \n642: #### Scenario IT-1.2: End-to-end pack for Java agent\n643: - **GIVEN** a Java workspace with valid structure\n644: - **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --language java`\n645: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n646:   - Successfully validate workspace\n647:   - Load or create metadata\n648:   - Process Java dependencies\n649:   - Generate Dockerfile\n650:   - Save updated metadata\n651:   - Display success message with paths\n652: \n653: #### Scenario IT-1.3: Pack with custom output path\n654: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace\n655: - **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube pack --output /custom/path`\n656: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n657:   - Successfully complete pack process\n658:   - Write metadata to custom output path\n659:   - Generate Dockerfile in custom output path\n660:   - Display success message with custom output path\n661: \n662: ### Error Handling Test Scenarios\n663: \n664: #### Scenario ET-1.1: Test error propagation\n665: - **GIVEN** various error conditions\n666: - **WHEN** errors occur during pack\n667: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n668:   - Missing workspace path raises appropriate error\n669:   - Invalid language raises validation error\n670:   - Invalid port raises validation error\n671:   - Invalid build_mode raises validation error\n672:   - Missing required metadata fields raise validation error\n673:   - CLI displays error message in red\n674:   - CLI exits with code 1\n675: \n676: ---\n677: \n678: ## Acceptance Criteria\n679: \n680: ### Functional Acceptance Criteria\n681: \n682: - [ ] Pack command accepts all documented options with correct types and defaults\n683: - [ ] Workspace structure validation correctly identifies valid and invalid workspaces\n684: - [ ] Metadata loading supports primary and fallback filenames\n685: - [ ] Metadata creation works for new workspaces\n686: - [ ] CLI option overrides correctly update metadata fields\n687: - [ ] Language-specific dependency processing works for Python and Java\n688: - [ ] Dockerfile generation produces valid Dockerfiles for Python and Java\n689: - [ ] Entrypoint inference correctly identifies default entrypoints\n690: - [ ] Metadata saving creates valid YAML with correct formatting\n691: - [ ] Output path handling supports default and custom paths\n692: - [ ] Success reporting displays all required information\n693: - [ ] Verbose mode provides detailed logging\n694: - [ ] Error handling displays appropriate messages and exits with code 1\n695: \n696: ### Non-Functional Acceptance Criteria\n697: \n698: - [ ] Pack command completes within reasonable time for typical workspaces\n699: - [ ] Memory usage remains reasonable for large workspaces\n700: - [ ] Path traversal protection prevents unauthorized access\n701: - [ ] Sensitive information in metadata is handled securely\n702: - [ ] Error messages are clear and actionable\n703: - [ ] Unit tests cover all major code paths\n704: - [ ] Integration tests cover end-to-end scenarios\n705: - [ ] Error handling tests verify proper error propagation and display\n706: \n707: ---\n708: \n709: ## Implementation Notes\n710: \n711: ### Key Components\n712: \n713: 1. **PackRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`)\n714:    - Main runtime class implementing pack logic\n715:    - Handles workspace validation, metadata processing, and Dockerfile generation\n716: \n717: 2. **MetadataService** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n718:    - Handles metadata loading and saving\n719:    - Provides validation methods for metadata fields\n720: \n721: 3. **AgentMetadata** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n722:    - Pydantic model for metadata validation\n723:    - Contains all agent configuration fields\n724: \n725: 4. **Typer CLI framework**\n726:    - Provides command-line interface definition\n727:    - Handles option parsing and validation\n728: \n729: 5. **Rich library**\n730:    - Provides formatted console output\n731:    - Supports progress spinners and colored text\n732: \n733: ### Key Algorithms\n734: \n735: #### Workspace Validation Algorithm\n736: 1. Check if workspace path exists\n737: 2. Verify path is a directory\n738: 3. Based on metadata.language or CLI option:\n739:    - For Python: verify at least one .py file exists\n740:    - For Java: verify pom.xml exists\n741: 4. Raise ValueError if any validation fails\n742: \n743: #### Metadata Loading Algorithm\n744: 1. Attempt to load agent_metadata.yaml\n745: 2. If not found, attempt to load agent.yaml\n746: 3. If not found, attempt to load metadata.yaml\n747: 4. If no file found, create new metadata with defaults\n748: 5. Parse YAML content into AgentMetadata model\n749: 6. Validate all fields using Pydantic validators\n750: 7. Return metadata object\n751: \n752: #### Option Override Algorithm\n753: 1. For each CLI option provided:\n754:    - Check if option value is not None\n755:    - Validate option value against type and range constraints\n756:    - Update corresponding metadata field\n757: 2. Return updated metadata\n758: \n759: #### Dockerfile Generation Algorithm\n760: 1. Determine language from metadata\n761: 2. Based on language:\n762:    - For Python: call _generate_python_dockerfile\n763:    - For Java: call _generate_java_dockerfile\n764: 3. Generate Dockerfile content with appropriate base image and steps\n765: 4. Write Dockerfile to workspace root\n766: 5. Return path to generated Dockerfile\n767: \n768: ---\n769: \n770: ## Related Requirements\n771: \n772: - **AR-021:** CLI build command (depends on pack command output)\n773: - **AR-022:** CLI publish command (depends on pack and build commands)\n774: - **AR-023:** CLI invoke command (depends on publish command)\n775: - **AR-024:** CLI status command (depends on publish command)\n\n(End of file - total 775 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# delta-spec.md — AR-020: CLI pack 命令\n\n## Module: `cmd/cli`\n\n## Delta Overview\n\nAdd the `pack` command to the AgentCube CLI for validating and preparing agent workspaces, merging CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generating Dockerfiles, and reporting paths.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Pack command initialization\n\n### Requirement: Pack command registration and default options\n\nSystem SHALL provide a `pack` command that validates and prepares agent workspaces with configurable options.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Command name: `pack`\n- Supports workspace path specification\n- Supports metadata field overrides via CLI options","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869274195,"end":1775869274216}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775869274251,"sessionID":"ses_285f33c83ffebugr45C3NGY0KM","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0ea86b001KgKupFUBe7dyQI","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a0e9d58001ybSUfmB2UVBP1j","sessionID":"ses_285f33c83ffebugr45C3NGY0KM","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":42696,"input":943,"output":90,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":41663}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775869277750,"sessionID":"ses_285f33c83ffebugr45C3NGY0KM","part":{"id":"prt_d7a0eb6320011mk6OzOPCQ45v7","messageID":"msg_d7a0ea8ae001IlhCMFtM61Csrx","sessionID":"ses_285f33c83ffebugr45C3NGY0KM","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869421410,"sessionID":"ses_285f33c83ffebugr45C3NGY0KM","part":{"id":"prt_d7a10e5bb001jUl8KQi3aqx62o","messageID":"msg_d7a0ea8ae001IlhCMFtM61Csrx","sessionID":"ses_285f33c83ffebugr45C3NGY0KM","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-d7ddecc32dc542e6bb054e350874967b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Specification: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status Commands\n\n## Module: `cmd/cli`\n\n## Language: Python\n\n## Size: M\n\n## Delta Overview\n\nAdd the `invoke` and `status` commands to the AgentCube CLI for sending payloads to deployed agents and checking their deployment status, supporting both AgentCube (AgentRuntime CR) and standard Kubernetes (Deployment/Service) providers.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Invoke command initialization\n\n### Requirement: Invoke command registration and default options\n\nSystem SHALL provide an `invoke` command that sends JSON payloads to deployed agent endpoints with configurable options.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Command name: `invoke`\n- Supports workspace path specification\n- Supports JSON payload specification\n- Supports custom HTTP headers\n- Supports provider selection (agentcube/k8s)\n- Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 1.1: Command registration and default options\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\n- **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube invoke` without options\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\n  - `workspace`: `\".\"` (current directory)\n  - `payload`: `\"{}\"` (empty JSON object)\n  - `header_list`: `None`\n  - `provider`: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `verbose`: `False`\n\n#### Scenario 1.2: Command option validation\n- **GIVEN** the user provides CLI options\n- **WHEN** options include `--workspace`, `--payload`, `--header`, `--provider`, `--verbose`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL accept all valid option values:\n  - `workspace`: string path to workspace directory\n  - `payload`: JSON-formatted string\n  - `header_list`: list of strings in \"key:value\" format\n  - `provider`: string (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n  - `verbose`: boolean flag\n\n---\n\n## REQ-002: Payload validation and parsing\n\n### Requirement: JSON payload validation\n\nSystem SHALL validate the payload format before invocation and provide clear error messages.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Validates JSON syntax before sending\n- Rejects invalid JSON with clear error message\n- Supports complex nested JSON structures\n- Exits with code 1 on invalid payload\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 2.1: Valid JSON payload\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a valid JSON payload string\n- **WHEN** `--payload '{\"query\": \"What is AI?\", \"context\": [\"ML\"]}'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Successfully parse it into a Python dictionary\n  - Pass it to the runtime\n  - Continue with invocation\n\n#### Scenario 2.2: Invalid JSON payload\n- **GIVEN** the user provides an invalid JSON payload\n- **WHEN** `--payload '{invalid json}'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print \"Invalid JSON payload\" in red\n  - Exit with code `1`\n  - NOT call `InvokeRuntime.invoke` or `_handle_error`\n\n#### Scenario 2.3: Empty payload default\n- **GIVEN** the user omits the `--payload` option\n- **WHEN** the command runs with default payload `\"{}\"`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Parse `\"{}\"` as an empty dictionary\n  - Pass empty dictionary to runtime\n\n#### Scenario 2.4: Complex nested payload\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a complex nested JSON structure\n- **WHEN** `--payload '{\"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello\"}], \"temperature\": 0.7, \"max_tokens\": 100}'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Preserve the full structure\n  - Pass it to the runtime\n\n---\n\n## REQ-003: Header format validation\n\n### Requirement: Custom header validation\n\nSystem SHALL validate custom header format and provide clear error messages for malformed headers.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Validates header format contains at least one colon\n- Rejects invalid format with clear error message\n- Supports headers with colons in values\n- Supports multiple header specifications\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 3.1: Valid header format\n- **GIVEN** the user provides correctly formatted headers\n- **WHEN** parsing `--header 'Authorization: Bearer token'` and `--header 'Content-Type: application/json'`\n- **THEN** each header SHALL be:\n  - Split at the first `:` into key and value\n\n#### Scenario 3.2: Invalid header without colon\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a header string without a colon separator\n- **WHEN** `--header 'InvalidHeader'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print \"Header must be in 'key:value' format\" in red\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario 3.3: Header with multiple colons\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a header with colons in the value\n- **WHEN** `--header 'Authorization: Bearer:token:with:colons'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Split only at the first `:`\n  - key = `\"Authorization\"`\n  - value = `\"Bearer:token:with:colons\"`\n\n#### Scenario 3.4: Empty header value\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a header with an empty value\n- **WHEN** `--header 'X-Custom-Header:'` is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - key = `\"X-Custom-Header\"`\n  - value = `\"\"` (empty string)\n\n#### Scenario 3.5: Multiple header specifications\n- **GIVEN** the user needs to pass multiple custom headers\n- **WHEN** the command is `invoke --header 'Authorization: Bearer token1' --header 'X-Custom-Header: value'`\n- **THEN** `header_list` SHALL be `['Authorization: Bearer token1', 'X-Custom-Header: value']`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-004: Session header management\n\n### Requirement: Automatic session ID header injection\n\nSystem SHALL automatically add the session ID header when metadata contains a `session_id`.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Automatically adds session header when session_id exists\n- Does not add session header when session_id is missing\n- Allows custom header to override metadata session_id\n- Uses correct header name spelling\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 4.1: Session ID from metadata\n- **GIVEN** the agent metadata contains `session_id: \"abc-123-def\"`\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs with this metadata\n- **THEN** the HTTP request SHALL include:\n  - Header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: abc-123-def`\n\n#### Scenario 4.2: No session ID in metadata\n- **GIVEN** the agent metadata does not contain a `session_id` field\n- **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n- **THEN** the HTTP request SHALL NOT include:\n  - The session header\n\n#### Scenario 4.3: Session ID override with custom header\n- **GIVEN** the metadata has `session_id: \"abc-123\"`\n- **WHEN** the user provides `--header 'X-Agentcube-Session-Id: custom-session'`\n- **THEN** the custom header value SHALL:\n  - Take precedence over the metadata session ID\n\n---\n\n## REQ-005: Workspace path resolution\n\n### Requirement: Path resolution for invoke\n\nSystem SHALL resolve the workspace path relative to the current working directory.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Resolves relative paths correctly\n- Handles absolute paths correctly\n- Uses current directory as default\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 5.1: Relative workspace path\n- **GIVEN** the user provides `-f ./my-agent`\n- **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n- **THEN** it SHALL be:\n  - Resolved to `{cwd}/my-agent`\n\n#### Scenario 5.2: Absolute workspace path\n- **GIVEN** the user provides `-f /absolute/path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n- **THEN** it SHALL remain:\n  - `/absolute/path/to/agent`\n\n#### Scenario 5.3: Default workspace path\n- **GIVEN** the user omits the `-f` option\n- **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n- **THEN** it SHALL be:\n  - The current working directory `\".\"`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-006: Provider-specific invocation\n\n### Requirement: Provider-based routing\n\nSystem SHALL route invocation requests to the appropriate endpoint based on the `provider` parameter.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Routes to AgentRuntime CR endpoint for agentcube provider\n- Routes to K8s service endpoint for k8s provider\n- Rewrites URL correctly for AgentRuntime invocations\n- Uses Router URL when available\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 6.1: AgentCube provider (default)\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"` (default)\n- **WHEN** the agent is deployed as an AgentRuntime CR\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load metadata and check for `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n  - Rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n  - Include session headers if present\n\n#### Scenario 6.2: Kubernetes provider\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"`\n- **WHEN** the agent is deployed as a standard K8s Deployment/Service\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use the service URL from metadata (e.g., `http://localhost:{node_port}`)\n  - NOT rewrite the URL to the AgentRuntime invocation path\n  - Direct POST to the agent's endpoint\n\n#### Scenario 6.3: AgentCube provider with Router URL\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n- **WHEN** metadata contains `router_url`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Use the Router URL for invocation\n  - Format as `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-007: Invoke prerequisites validation\n\n### Requirement: Pre-invocation validation\n\nSystem SHALL validate that all prerequisites are met before attempting invocation.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Validates agent is published (has agent_id)\n- Validates metadata file exists\n- Validates workspace path exists\n- Validates provider value is valid\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 7.1: Agent not published\n- **GIVEN** the workspace metadata lacks `agent_id`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise an error indicating the agent must be published first\n\n#### Scenario 7.2: Missing metadata file\n- **GIVEN** the workspace directory exists\n- **WHEN** it has no `agent_metadata.yaml` (or fallbacks)\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise an error indicating metadata file is missing\n\n#### Scenario 7.3: Invalid workspace path\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise a `ValueError` indicating the directory does not exist\n\n#### Scenario 7.4: Invalid provider value\n- **GIVEN** the user provides an invalid provider value\n- **WHEN** `--provider invalid-provider` is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Validate and reject the provider value\n\n---\n\n## REQ-008: Invoke response handling\n\n### Requirement: Response processing and display\n\nSystem SHALL handle and display invocation responses appropriately.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Displays successful responses in readable format\n- Displays error responses with details\n- Handles network timeouts gracefully\n- Formats JSON responses properly\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 8.1: Successful invocation\n- **GIVEN** the agent endpoint returns a successful response (2xx)\n- **WHEN** the invocation completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print the response in a formatted manner\n\n#### Scenario 8.2: Agent returns error response\n- **GIVEN** the agent endpoint returns an error response (4xx or 5xx)\n- **WHEN** the invocation completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Display the error message\n  - Display response details\n\n#### Scenario 8.3: Network timeout\n- **GIVEN** the invocation request times out\n- **WHEN** the timeout period elapses\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise a timeout exception\n  - Handle exception via `_handle_error`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-009: Error handling for invoke\n\n### Requirement: Consistent error handling\n\nSystem SHALL use consistent error handling patterns for all exceptions.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Catches runtime exceptions\n- Displays error messages in red\n- Shows tracebacks in verbose mode\n- Exits with code 1 on errors\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 9.1: Runtime exception\n- **GIVEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` raises a `RuntimeError`\n- **WHEN** the exception is caught by the CLI\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n  - Print \"Error invoke: {error_message}\" in red\n  - If `verbose` is `True`, print the full traceback\n  - Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n\n#### Scenario 9.2: HTTP connection error\n- **GIVEN** there is a network connectivity issue\n- **WHEN** the invocation attempt fails\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Catch the connection error\n  - Surface it via `_handle_error`\n\n#### Scenario 9.3: Subcommand verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** the user uses the local `--verbose` flag on the `invoke` command\n- **WHEN** an error occurs\n- **THEN** the traceback SHALL be:\n  - Printed even if the global `-v` was not passed\n\n---\n\n## REQ-010: Status command initialization\n\n### Requirement: Status command registration and default options\n\nSystem SHALL provide a `status` command that displays the current state of a deployed agent.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Command name: `status`\n- Supports workspace path specification\n- Supports provider selection (agentcube/k8s)\n- Provides verbose mode for detailed logging\n- Displays status in formatted table\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 10.1: Command registration and default options\n- **GIVEN** the AgentCube CLI Typer application is initialized\n- **WHEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube status` without options\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use these defaults:\n  - `workspace`: `\".\"` (current directory)\n  - `provider`: `\"agentcube\"`\n  - `verbose`: `False`\n\n#### Scenario 10.2: Custom workspace and provider\n- **GIVEN** the user specifies custom options\n- **WHEN** parsing `status -f /path/to/workspace --provider k8s`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use:\n  - `workspace`: `\"/path/to/workspace\"`\n  - `provider`: `\"k8s\"`\n  - `verbose`: `False`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-011: Status display formatting\n\n### Requirement: Rich table formatting\n\nSystem SHALL display agent status in a Rich `Table` with clear, readable formatting.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Displays status in Rich table\n- Shows key information fields\n- Handles missing fields gracefully\n- Provides clear status indication\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 11.1: Successful status retrieval\n- **GIVEN** the agent is successfully deployed and status is available\n- **WHEN** `status` runs and retrieves status information\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n  - A Rich `Table` containing:\n    - Field names in the first column\n    - Field values in the second column\n    - Key information: agent name, namespace, status, endpoint, deployment details\n\n#### Scenario 11.2: Status table fields\n- **GIVEN** the agent status is retrieved\n- **WHEN** the Rich table is rendered\n- **THEN** it SHALL include these fields when available:\n  - Agent Name\n  - Namespace\n  - Status (e.g., \"running\", \"ready\", \"error\", \"not_published\")\n  - Agent Endpoint\n  - Session ID (if applicable)\n  - Deployment Type (AgentRuntime or Deployment/Service)\n  - Image URL\n  - Version\n\n#### Scenario 11.3: Status not published\n- **GIVEN** the agent metadata has no `agent_id` field\n- **WHEN** `status` is called and returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print a message indicating the agent is not published\n  - Provide guidance to run `publish` command first\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-012: Status for AgentCube provider\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime CR status retrieval\n\nSystem SHALL retrieve and display status for agents deployed via the AgentCube provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Retrieves status from AgentRuntime CR\n- Handles CR with status field\n- Handles CR without status field\n- Handles CR not found\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 12.1: AgentRuntime CR with status\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists with status\n- **THEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` SHALL:\n  - Read status from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present\n  - Extract `status` and `agentEndpoint` from the CR status\n\n#### Scenario 12.2: AgentRuntime CR created but no status\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists but has no status field\n- **THEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` SHALL:\n  - Return status `\"created_no_status\"`\n\n#### Scenario 12.3: AgentRuntime CR not found\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntime CR does not exist\n- **THEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` SHALL:\n  - Return status `\"not_found_in_k8s\"`\n\n#### Scenario 12.4: AgentRuntime CR error status\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR status indicates an error condition\n- **WHEN** status is retrieved\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Display error details\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-013: Status for Kubernetes provider\n\n### Requirement: K8s Deployment/Service status retrieval\n\nSystem SHALL retrieve and display status for agents deployed via the standard Kubernetes provider.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Queries both Deployment and Service status\n- Displays deployment ready replicas\n- Displays service node port and URL\n- Handles resources not found\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 13.1: K8s deployment and service status\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"`\n- **WHEN** the agent is deployed with Deployment and Service\n- **THEN** `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` SHALL:\n  - Query both Deployment and Service status\n  - Include:\n    - Deployment ready replicas\n    - Service node port\n    - Service URL\n    - Pod status summary\n\n#### Scenario 13.2: K8s deployment not ready\n- **GIVEN** the Deployment exists but replicas are not ready\n- **WHEN** status is retrieved\n- **THEN** the status SHALL indicate:\n  - `\"not_ready\"` with details about current vs. desired replicas\n\n#### Scenario 13.3: K8s resources not found\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"k8s\"`\n- **WHEN** neither Deployment nor Service exists\n- **THEN** the status SHALL indicate:\n  - `\"not_found_in_k8s\"`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-014: Status exit codes\n\n### Requirement: Appropriate exit codes\n\nSystem SHALL use appropriate exit codes to indicate the result of status checks.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Exit code 0 for success/ready\n- Exit code 1 for failure/not-ready/not-published\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 14.1: Successful status (agent running)\n- **GIVEN** the agent status indicates it is running or ready\n- **WHEN** `status` completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with:\n  - code `0`\n\n#### Scenario 14.2: Agent not published\n- **GIVEN** the agent has no `agent_id` in metadata\n- **WHEN** `status` completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with:\n  - code `1`\n\n#### Scenario 14.3: Agent in error state\n- **GIVEN** the agent status indicates an error condition\n- **WHEN** `status` completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with:\n  - code `1`\n\n#### Scenario 14.4: Agent not found in Kubernetes\n- **GIVEN** the agent was previously published but the CR or Deployment no longer exists\n- **WHEN** `status` completes\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with:\n  - code `1`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-015: Workspace path resolution for status\n\n### Requirement: Path resolution for status\n\nSystem SHALL resolve the workspace path for status checks.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Uses current directory as default\n- Resolves custom paths correctly\n- Validates path existence\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 15.1: Default workspace\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status` without `-f` option\n- **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n- **THEN** it SHALL use:\n  - The current working directory `\".\"`\n\n#### Scenario 15.2: Custom workspace path\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status -f /path/to/agent`\n- **WHEN** the workspace path is resolved\n- **THEN** it SHALL use:\n  - `/path/to/agent`\n\n#### Scenario 15.3: Missing workspace\n- **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n- **WHEN** `status` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise a `ValueError` indicating the directory does not exist\n\n---\n\n## REQ-016: Verbose logging for status\n\n### Requirement: Detailed logging support\n\nSystem SHALL provide detailed logging when verbose mode is enabled.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Logs Kubernetes API calls\n- Logs resource retrieval\n- Logs status parsing\n- Logs warnings and additional information\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 16.1: Verbose status output\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `status --verbose`\n- **WHEN** status is retrieved\n- **THEN** the system SHALL log:\n  - Additional details about Kubernetes API calls\n  - CR or resource retrieval\n  - Status parsing\n  - Any warnings or additional information\n\n---\n\n## REQ-017: Error handling for status\n\n### Requirement: Consistent error handling\n\nSystem SHALL use consistent error handling patterns for all exceptions.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Catches runtime exceptions\n- Displays error messages in red\n- Shows tracebacks in verbose mode\n- Exits with code 1 on errors\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 17.1: Status retrieval exception\n- **GIVEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` raises a `RuntimeError`\n- **WHEN** the exception is caught by the CLI\n- **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL:\n  - Print \"Error status: {error_message}\" in red\n  - If `verbose` is `True`, print the full traceback\n  - Exit with code `1` via `typer.Exit(1)`\n\n#### Scenario 17.2: Kubernetes connection error\n- **GIVEN** there is an issue connecting to the Kubernetes API\n- **WHEN** `status` attempts to query the cluster\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Catch the connection error\n  - Surface it via `_handle_error`\n\n#### Scenario 17.3: Metadata validation error\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but contains invalid data\n- **WHEN** `status` attempts to load metadata\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Catch the validation error\n  - Surface it via `_handle_error`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-018: Metadata file loading\n\n### Requirement: Metadata loading with fallback\n\nSystem SHALL load agent metadata from the workspace with appropriate fallback behavior.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Loads from agent_metadata.yaml first\n- Falls back to agent.yaml\n- Falls back to metadata.yaml\n- Raises error if none found\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 18.1: Primary metadata file exists\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** metadata is loaded for `invoke` or `status`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load from `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario 18.2: Primary missing, first fallback\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `agent.yaml` does exist\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load from `agent.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario 18.3: Primary and first fallback missing\n- **GIVEN** neither `agent_metadata.yaml` nor `agent.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** `metadata.yaml` does exist\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load from `metadata.yaml`\n\n#### Scenario 18.4: No metadata file found\n- **GIVEN** no metadata file exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** metadata is loaded\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise an error indicating no metadata file was found\n\n---\n\n## REQ-019: Global verbose logging propagation\n\n### Requirement: Verbose flag propagation\n\nSystem SHALL correctly propagate verbose logging settings from the root callback to subcommands.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Global verbose enables logging for all subcommands\n- Subcommand verbose enables logging for that subcommand\n- Combination of both works correctly\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 19.1: Global verbose with subcommand verbose\n- **GIVEN** the user passes both global `-v` and local `--verbose` on `invoke` or `status`\n- **WHEN** the command runs\n- **THEN** verbose logging SHALL be:\n  - Enabled\n\n#### Scenario 19.2: Subcommand verbose without global verbose\n- **GIVEN** the user passes only `invoke --verbose` without global `-v`\n- **WHEN** the command runs\n- **THEN** verbose logging SHALL be:\n  - Enabled for that subcommand\n\n#### Scenario 19.3: Global verbose without subcommand verbose\n- **GIVEN** the user passes only global `-v` without subcommand `--verbose`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` or `status` runs\n- **THEN** verbose logging SHALL be:\n  - Enabled\n\n---\n\n## REQ-020: Rich output formatting\n\n### Requirement: Consistent Rich library usage\n\nSystem SHALL use Rich library for consistent, readable command output.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Uses Rich table for status\n- Uses Rich console for errors\n- Uses Rich progress spinner for long operations\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 20.1: Rich table for status\n- **GIVEN** status information is available\n- **WHEN** displaying status\n- **THEN** the output SHALL be:\n  - Formatted as a Rich table with proper styling\n\n#### Scenario 20.2: Rich console for errors\n- **GIVEN** an error occurs\n- **WHEN** the error is displayed\n- **THEN** error messages SHALL use:\n  - Rich console for red-colored output\n\n#### Scenario 20.3: Rich progress spinner\n- **GIVEN** a long-running operation\n- **WHEN** the operation is in progress\n- **THEN** the system SHALL display:\n  - A Rich Progress spinner\n\n---\n\n## Integration Scenarios\n\n### INT-001: Full workflow - pack, build, publish, invoke\n\n#### Scenario INT-1.1: Complete lifecycle\n- **GIVEN** a valid agent workspace\n- **WHEN** the user runs:\n  1. `pack` - successfully packages the workspace\n  2. `build` - successfully builds the image\n  3. `publish --provider agentcube` - successfully deploys to Kubernetes\n  4. `invoke --payload '{\"query\": \"test\"}'` - sends a payload\n- **THEN** each command SHALL:\n  - Complete successfully\n  - `invoke` SHALL receive a response from the deployed agent\n\n#### Scenario INT-1.2: Invoke after local build publish\n- **GIVEN** an agent built in local mode\n- **WHEN** published with `--image-url` and `--provider k8s`\n- **THEN** `invoke --provider k8s` SHALL:\n  - Successfully send requests to the NodePort service\n\n### INT-002: Status checks during deployment lifecycle\n\n#### Scenario INT-2.1: Status before publish\n- **GIVEN** an agent has been packed but not published\n- **WHEN** `status` is run\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Indicate the agent is not published\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n#### Scenario INT-2.2: Status during deployment rollout\n- **GIVEN** an agent has been published and is in the process of becoming ready\n- **WHEN** `status` is run\n- **THEN** the system SHALL show:\n  - The current deployment state (e.g., \"not_ready\")\n\n#### Scenario INT-2.3: Status after agent is ready\n- **GIVEN** an agent deployment has completed successfully\n- **WHEN** `status` is run\n- **THEN** the system SHALL show:\n  - Status \"ready\" or \"running\" with full endpoint information\n\n### INT-003: Session management across invokes\n\n#### Scenario INT-3.1: Reuse session ID from metadata\n- **GIVEN** the first `invoke` establishes a session\n- **WHEN** it saves `session_id` to metadata\n- **THEN** subsequent `invoke` commands SHALL:\n  - Use the existing `session_id` from metadata\n\n#### Scenario INT-3.2: Session ID in headers\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id: \"existing-session\"`\n- **WHEN** `invoke` is called with `--header 'X-Agentcube-Session-Id: new-session'`\n- **THEN** the custom header SHALL:\n  - Override the metadata session ID for that specific request\n\n---\n\n## Edge Cases and Error Conditions\n\n### EDGE-001: Malformed metadata\n\n#### Scenario EDGE-1.1: Missing required fields\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file exists but lacks required fields\n- **WHEN** `invoke` or `status` attempts to load metadata\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise a validation error indicating which fields are missing\n\n#### Scenario EDGE-1.2: Invalid data types in metadata\n- **GIVEN** the metadata file contains fields with invalid data types\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise a validation error with details about the type mismatch\n\n### EDGE-002: Concurrent invocations\n\n#### Scenario EDGE-2.1: Multiple invocations in parallel\n- **GIVEN** an agent is deployed and ready\n- **WHEN** multiple `invoke` commands are run simultaneously\n- **THEN** each invocation SHALL:\n  - Receive its own response\n  - Have session headers correctly applied to each request\n\n### EDGE-003: Large payloads\n\n#### Scenario EDGE-3.1: Large JSON payload\n- **GIVEN** the user provides a large JSON payload (e.g., 1MB)\n- **WHEN** `invoke --payload` is called with the large payload\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Successfully parse and send the payload to the agent endpoint\n\n#### Scenario EDGE-3.2: Extremely large payload rejection\n- **GIVEN** the user provides an extremely large JSON payload exceeding system limits\n- **WHEN** `invoke --payload` is called\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Reject the payload with an appropriate error message\n\n---\n\n## Provider-specific Edge Cases\n\n### EDGE-004: AgentCube provider edge cases\n\n#### Scenario EDGE-4.1: Missing router_url\n- **GIVEN** `provider` is `\"agentcube\"`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Raise an error indicating `router_url` is required for AgentCube provider\n\n#### Scenario EDGE-4.2: AgentRuntime CR with missing status field\n- **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists\n- **WHEN** it has no status field in its spec\n- **THEN** `status` SHALL:\n  - Handle gracefully and return appropriate status\n\n### EDGE-005: Kubernetes provider edge cases\n\n#### Scenario EDGE-5.1: NodePort outside valid range\n- **GIVEN** a K8s deployment was created with an invalid NodePort\n- **WHEN** `invoke --provider k8s` attempts to connect\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Handle connection errors appropriately\n\n#### Scenario EDGE-5.2: Service with no endpoints\n- **GIVEN** the K8s Service exists\n- **WHEN** it has no ready endpoints\n- **THEN** `invoke --provider k8s` SHALL:\n  - Handle connection errors\n  - Provide informative messages\n\n---\n\n## Technical Constraints\n\n### Requirement: Language and dependencies\n\nSystem SHALL use Python 3.10+ and the following dependencies:\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `typer[all]>=0.9.0` for CLI framework\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` for data validation\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` for YAML parsing\n- `httpx>=0.24.0` for HTTP client\n- `rich>=13.0.0` for formatted console output\n- `kubernetes>=28.0.0` for Kubernetes API client (optional)\n\n### Requirement: File locations\n\n- CLI command definition: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n- InvokeRuntime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n- StatusRuntime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n- MetadataService implementation: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n- Metadata filename: `agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n### Requirement: Exit codes\n\nSystem SHALL return appropriate exit codes:\n- Exit code 0 for successful operations\n- Exit code 1 for failures\n- Exit code 130 for SIGINT (Ctrl+C) interruption\n\n---\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n### Unit Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.1: Test payload validation\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for payload validation\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Valid JSON payload parsing\n  - Invalid JSON payload rejection\n  - Empty payload default handling\n  - Complex nested payload parsing\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.2: Test header validation\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for header validation\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Valid header format parsing\n  - Invalid header format rejection\n  - Multiple headers handling\n  - Headers with colons in values\n  - Empty header values\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.3: Test session header management\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for session header management\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - Session header injection when session_id exists\n  - No session header when session_id is missing\n  - Custom header override of session_id\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.4: Test provider routing\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for provider routing\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - AgentCube provider URL rewriting\n  - K8s provider direct routing\n  - Router URL usage for AgentCube provider\n\n#### Scenario UT-1.5: Test status retrieval\n- **GIVEN** a test suite for status retrieval\n- **WHEN** tests run\n- **THEN** tests SHALL cover:\n  - AgentRuntime CR status retrieval\n  - K8s Deployment/Service status retrieval\n  - CR not found handling\n  - CR without status handling\n  - Resources not found handling\n\n### Integration Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario IT-1.1: End-to-end invoke for AgentCube provider\n- **GIVEN** a deployed agent with AgentRuntime CR\n- **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube invoke --payload '{\"test\": \"data\"}'`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load metadata from workspace\n  - Construct correct invocation URL\n  - Send payload with proper headers\n  - Receive and display response\n\n#### Scenario IT-1.2: End-to-end invoke for K8s provider\n- **GIVEN** a deployed agent with Deployment/Service\n- **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube invoke --provider k8s --payload '{\"test\": \"data\"}'`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load metadata from workspace\n  - Use service URL for invocation\n  - Send payload with proper headers\n  - Receive and display response\n\n#### Scenario IT-1.3: End-to-end status for AgentCube provider\n- **GIVEN** a deployed agent with AgentRuntime CR\n- **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube status`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load metadata from workspace\n  - Query AgentRuntime CR\n  - Display status in Rich table\n  - Exit with appropriate code\n\n#### Scenario IT-1.4: End-to-end status for K8s provider\n- **GIVEN** a deployed agent with Deployment/Service\n- **WHEN** user runs `kubectl-agentcube status --provider k8s`\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Load metadata from workspace\n  - Query Deployment and Service\n  - Display status in Rich table\n  - Exit with appropriate code\n\n### Error Handling Test Scenarios\n\n#### Scenario ET-1.1: Test error propagation for invoke\n- **GIVEN** various error conditions for invoke\n- **WHEN** errors occur during invocation\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Invalid JSON payload displays error and exits with code 1\n  - Invalid header format displays error and exits with code 1\n  - Agent not published displays error and exits with code 1\n  - Network errors are caught and surfaced\n  - CLI displays error message in red\n  - CLI shows traceback in verbose mode\n\n#### Scenario ET-1.2: Test error propagation for status\n- **GIVEN** various error conditions for status\n- **WHEN** errors occur during status check\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Agent not published displays guidance and exits with code 1\n  - Kubernetes connection errors are caught and surfaced\n  - Metadata validation errors are caught and surfaced\n  - CLI displays error message in red\n  - CLI shows traceback in verbose mode\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Invoke Command\n\n- [ ] Invoke command accepts all documented options with correct types and defaults\n- [ ] Invalid JSON payloads are rejected with clear error messages\n- [ ] Invalid header formats are rejected with clear error messages\n- [ ] Session headers are automatically added when session_id exists in metadata\n- [ ] Workspace paths are resolved correctly (relative and absolute)\n- [ ] AgentCube provider routes to AgentRuntime invocation endpoint\n- [ ] K8s provider routes directly to service endpoint\n- [ ] Prerequisites are validated before invocation attempts\n- [ ] Successful responses are displayed in a readable format\n- [ ] Error responses and timeouts are handled gracefully\n- [ ] Verbose mode provides detailed logging and traces\n- [ ] Exit code 0 on success, 1 on failure\n\n### Functional Acceptance Criteria - Status Command\n\n- [ ] Status command accepts all documented options with correct types and defaults\n- [ ] Status is displayed in a Rich table with clear formatting\n- [ ] \"Not published\" state is detected and reported with guidance\n- [ ] AgentRuntime CR status is correctly retrieved and parsed\n- [ ] K8s Deployment/Service status is correctly retrieved and parsed\n- [ ] Exit code 0 on success/ready, 1 on failure/not-ready/not-published\n- [ ] Workspace paths are resolved correctly\n- [ ] Verbose mode provides additional debugging information\n- [ ] Errors are caught and surfaced via _handle_error\n\n### Non-Functional Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Invoke command completes within reasonable time for typical payloads\n- [ ] Status command completes within reasonable time for typical queries\n- [ ] Memory usage remains reasonable for large payloads\n- [ ] Path traversal protection prevents unauthorized access\n- [ ] Sensitive information in headers is handled securely\n- [ ] Error messages are clear and actionable\n- [ ] Unit tests cover all major code paths\n- [ ] Integration tests cover end-to-end scenarios\n- [ ] Error handling tests verify proper error propagation and display\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Key Components\n\n1. **InvokeRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n   - Main runtime class implementing invoke logic\n   - Handles payload validation, header processing, and HTTP requests\n   - Routes to appropriate provider endpoints\n\n2. **StatusRuntime** (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n   - Main runtime class implementing status logic\n   - Handles AgentRuntime CR and K8s resource queries\n   - Formats status output for display\n\n3. **MetadataService** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n   - Handles metadata loading and saving\n   - Provides validation methods for metadata fields\n\n4. **AgentMetadata** (`agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`)\n   - Pydantic model for metadata validation\n   - Contains all agent configuration fields\n\n5. **Typer CLI framework**\n   - Provides command-line interface definition\n   - Handles option parsing and validation\n\n6. **Rich library**\n   - Provides formatted console output\n   - Supports tables, progress spinners, and colored text\n\n### Key Algorithms\n\n#### Invoke Algorithm\n1. Load metadata from workspace\n2. Validate agent is published (has agent_id)\n3. Parse JSON payload (validate syntax)\n4. Parse custom headers (validate format)\n5. Determine provider (agentcube or k8s)\n6. Construct invocation URL based on provider\n7. Add session header if session_id exists in metadata\n8. Send HTTP POST request with payload and headers\n9. Handle response or error\n10. Display result or error message\n\n#### Status Algorithm\n1. Load metadata from workspace\n2. Check if agent is published (has agent_id)\n3. Determine provider (agentcube or k8s)\n4. For agentcube provider:\n   - Query AgentRuntime CR\n   - Extract status and endpoint from CR\n5. For k8s provider:\n   - Query Deployment and Service\n   - Extract deployment and service status\n6. Format status information in Rich table\n7. Display table to user\n8. Exit with appropriate code\n\n#### Header Parsing Algorithm\n1. For each header string in header_list:\n   - Split at first `:` to get key and value\n   - Validate split produced exactly 2 parts\n   - If not, raise error with format message\n2. Return dictionary of key-value pairs\n\n#### Session Header Injection Algorithm\n1. Check if metadata.session_id exists and is truthy\n2. If yes, add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id: {session_id}`\n3. Check if custom headers already contain this header\n4. If custom headers exist, they take precedence\n5. Return final headers dictionary\n\n---\n\n## Related Requirements\n\n- **AR-020:** CLI pack command (required before invoke/status)\n- **AR-021:** CLI build command (required before invoke/status)\n- **AR-022:** CLI publish command (required before invoke/status)\n- **AR-024:** CLI additional commands (future work)\n- **cli-toolkit/spec.md:** Base CLI specifications\n- **deployment/client-go.md:** Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime CR\n- **python-sdk/spec.md:** SDK requirements and HTTP contracts","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869421067,"end":1775869421407}}}}
